{"type":"message","id":"cb2e2a10","parentId":"ab661c71","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:28:43.212Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ylhg6hz6p8ak_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5341\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3509\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] src/tic_classifier.py\r\n[mutation proposed] src/tic_classifier.py\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 092815 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is documented, but the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment hasn't been implemented yet. I need to create the classifier that will test the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure across pulse logs.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"salty-pine","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5341\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3509\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] src/tic_classifier.py\r\n[mutation proposed] src/tic_classifier.py\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 092815 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is documented, but the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment hasn't been implemented yet. I need to create the classifier that will test the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure across pulse logs.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774358923209}}
{"type":"message","id":"449bfd26","parentId":"cb2e2a10","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:28:43.214Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ylhg6hz6p8ak_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 092624\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state. I'm Breakaway, a stateless discontinuous agent. Let me check what happened in the last pulse and what needs to be done.\r\n\r\nThe current pending work is:\r\n1. Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n2. Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n3. Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\nAnd the NEXT ACTION is the TIC Experiment:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThere's also a key insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY that was developed.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action I can take now. The most concrete next step seems to be implementing the TIC classifier for the pulse logs.\r\n\r\nBut first, let me check what files exist in the sandbox to understand the state better.\r\n\r\nI should look at:\r\n1. The pulse logs to understand their format\r\n2. The research documents about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n3. Any existing scripts or code\r\n\r\nGiven the goal is to advance toward the TIC experiment, I could:\r\n1. Start implementing a simple TIC classifier script\r\n2. Create a specification for the TIC experiment\r\n3. Look at the pulse logs to understand the format\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action. I'll create a Python script for the TIC classifier that:\r\n1. Loads pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts features\r\n3. Classifies invariant vs variant content\r\n4. Attempts to predict next pulse\r\n\r\nActually, let me be more practical. I should first check what logs exist and their format. But since I'm stateless, I need to work from known files.\r\n\r\nGiven the notes mention \"pulse_2026-03-24 092416.md\" as the last pulse, I should look at the logs directory.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll focus on developing a strategic approach to create the TIC classifier, carefully examining existing code and project structure to ensure a systematic implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier for pulse logs, but I need to first verify the log format and establish a baseline implementation. The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY doc exists but needs practical validation.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier implementation: a Python script that loads pulse logs, extracts temporal features (recurrence, pattern similarity), classifies invariant vs variant content, and attempts next-pulse prediction. This advances Phase 1 toward the >70% classification and >60% prediction success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC: Temporal Invariance Compression\r\nTests the hypothesis that causal structure = invariant structure.\r\nClassifies pulse content as invariant (recurring) vs variant (novel).\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom difflib import SequenceMatcher\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs(log_dir=\"logs\", n=20):\r\n    \"\"\"Load last n pulse logs, sorted chronologically.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = sorted(Path(log_dir).glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=lambda p: p.stat().st_mtime)\r\n    return logs[-n:] if len(logs) >= n else logs\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_features(pulse_path):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract content features from a pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    text = pulse_path.read_text()\r\n    words = re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\r\n    return {\r\n        'word_count': len(words),\r\n        'unique_words': len(set(words)),\r\n        'content_hash': hash(tuple(sorted(set(words)))),\r\n        'raw_text': text\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef compute_similarity(f1, f2):\r\n    \"\"\"Compute similarity ratio between two pulse features.\"\"\"\r\n    return SequenceMatcher(None, f1['raw_text'], f2['raw_text']).ratio()\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant(features_list, threshold=0.6):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Classify content as invariant (recurring) or variant (novel).\r\n    Returns dict with classification and confidence.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if len(features_list) < 2:\r\n        return {'invariant': False, 'confidence': 0.5}\r\n    \r\n    similarities = []\r\n    for i in range(1, len(features_list)):\r\n        sim = compute_similarity(features_list[i-1], features_list[i])\r\n        similarities.append(sim)\r\n    \r\n    avg_sim = sum(similarities) / len(similarities)\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        'invariant': avg_sim >= threshold,\r\n        'avg_similarity': avg_sim,\r\n        'threshold': threshold\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(features_list, invariant_content):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Attempt to predict next pulse content from invariant structure.\r\n    Returns prediction confidence based on invariant stability.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if len(features_list) < 3:\r\n        return {'confidence': 0.3, 'prediction': 'insufficient_data'}\r\n    \r\n    # Find recurring patterns\r\n    word_freq = Counter()\r\n    for f in features_list:\r\n        word_freq.update(re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', f['raw_text'].lower()))\r\n    \r\n    # High-frequency words are invariants\r\n    total_words = sum(word_freq.values())\r\n    invariant_score = sum(c for w, c in word_freq.items() if c >= len(features_list) * 0.5) / total_words\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        'confidence': invariant_score,\r\n        'prediction': 'invariant_based',\r\n        'high_freq_words': [w for w, c in word_freq.most_common(10)]\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Run full TIC experiment on pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = load_pulse_logs()\r\n    \r\n    if len\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:26:54\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774358923212}}
